# Database (PostgreSQL)

## Connections

- **Runtime API:** `DATABASE_URL` (transaction pooler, port 6543)
- **Migrations/CLI:** `DIRECT_URL` (direct or session pooler, port 5432)
- Never run migrations against pgbouncer transaction pooler

## Design

- Add indexes for `where`, `orderBy`, foreign keys, status columns
- Use unique constraints on natural keys (`email`, `phone`)
- Cascade deletes explicit on relations — avoid orphan rows

## Query rules

- Never fetch entire tables without pagination
- Cap list `limit` (max 100) at validation layer
- Batch writes inside `$transaction`
- Avoid offset pagination on very large tables when cursor-based is needed later

## Never

- Raw SQL with string interpolation (`$queryRaw` with template vars is OK for static queries only)
- Duplicate identical queries in one request — use `Promise.all` when independent
